What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

The inspiration behind this video: 

After James Gunn became co-CEO of DC Studios with Peter Safran, he made huge moves signaling a more exciting future for DC, which included the announcement of Supergirl: Woman of Tomorrow for the DC Universe. Ever since 2013's Man of Steel, the DCEU has faced tonal and behind-the-scenes issues. The DC Universe provides a new way forward for the superhero franchise, especially since Gunn seemingly has a clear overarching vision for the franchise, which includes a long-awaited Supergirl film installment among other upcoming DC movies.

Supergirl might not be the most famous DC superhero, but the character has never gotten the justice she deserves, as the 1984 movie was a critical disaster and a box office bomb (via Box Office Mojo). And while she has had a small-screen hit, as the CW series Supergirl lasted for six seasons, that was very much a made-for-TV production. As such, Supergirl: Woman of Tomorrow is a great chance for the hero and her story to come to life, capitalizing on the character's history to further flesh out the DC Universe's Chapter 1.

Thank You So Much For Watching!

snippet.description:

Stream Breach: https://top.lnk.to/breach
Stream "RAWFEAR”: https://top.lnk.to/breach

LYRICS
RAWFEAR moves me,
Sounds of empty uzis,
Life is just forever nipping heels,
Never slowing down,
RAWFEAR moves me,
Sounds of empty uzis,
Life is just forever gripping feels,
Never slowing down.
 
You know what scares me?
Nah, it’s stupid,
You’ve met my fears,
They’re all regulars,
Wait, who’s the new kid?
You know what kills me?
Not getting stronger,
And now I can’t seem to sit still any longer.

Learning all that really matters is a slow and painful lesson,
It is not ‘pass’ or ‘fail’, but a poisonous progression,
Try to micro-dose to immunity but you’ll never, ever get it,
And I go,
‘What’s the matter?’ Isn’t helping,
I wish her parents would stop yelling,
I could build a tower with the times I was pretending,
Try to micro-dose to immunity but I’ll never see the ending,
‘What’s the matter?’ Isn’t helping,
I wish her parents would stop yelling.

snippet.title: Avengers: Doomsday - First Trailer (2026) Robert Downey Jr | Marvel Studios
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Avengers: Doomsday

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story positions the MCU on the brink of its greatest unraveling as Victor Von Doom, played with chilling precision by Robert Downey Jr., emerges as a multiversal force intent on reshaping existence itself. The fractures between realities draw in every corner of Marvel’s evolving landscape: Sam Wilson’s uneasy leadership, the rise of the New Avengers, the long-awaited arrival of the Fantastic Four in pursuit of a threat tied to Franklin Richards, and the return of the Fox-era X-Men led by icons like Professor X and Magneto. Old tensions resurface, new alliances form under pressure, and Loki’s ascension as guardian of the timelines places him directly in Doom’s path, setting the stage for a conflict that is both cosmic in scope and uncomfortably personal. As incursions escalate and the boundaries between worlds dissolve, the stakes surpass anything the Avengers have faced before, signaling the opening chapter of the Multiverse Saga’s climactic end.

snippet.title: Can I Beat An Impossible Game?
snippet.description:
Video games are fantastic and I love playing them but after a decade of professionally breaking them I must say they have gotten very easy. It does not help that certain publishers like ubisoft and EA seem obsessed with turning the default difficulty into a frictionless experience with incredible hand holding that removes the suspense and purpose of the game. That brings me to the focus today. A game that on the normal difficulty is an absolute walk in the park but thanks to some modifications I have made the game is now a proper stealth action fps with an experience that no other game can compete with! 

So today I am setting up an impossible challenge in a game with the most extreme permadeath difficulty I have dealt with when failure is inevitable and incredibly easy. So Can the spiffing brit beat this challenge or is it truly an impossible game!

Chapters:
02:00 - What is Going On
38:00 - The Meat and Potatos
39:40 - Outro

It does not help that certain publishers like ubisoft and EA seem obsessed with turning the default difficulty into a frictionless experience with incredible hand holding that removes the suspense and purpose of the game. That brings me to the focus today. A game that on the normal difficulty is an absolute walk in the park but thanks to some modifications I have made the game is now a proper stealth action fps with an experience that no other game can compete with! 

So today I am setting up an impossible challenge in a game with the most extreme permadeath difficulty I have dealt with when failure is inevitable and incredibly easy. So Can the spiffing brit beat this challenge or is it truly an impossible game!

Chapters:
02:00 - What is Going On
38:00 - The Meat and Potatos
39:40 - Outro
